          h3 Flavours of causality

          ul
            li.fragment Graphical models: Pearl and many others
              ul.fragment
                li Vanilla Bayesian networks: Time as an afterthought
                li Dynamic Bayesian networks: Hard to model long-term effects and non-discrete intervals
            li.fragment Granger-causality: Can past values of X be used to forecast Y?
              ul
                li Not really causality, more like temporal correlation
            li.fragment
              | Kleinberg: Temporal logic, cause precedes effect and raises its probability, causal significance across
